================================================================================
1. SUMMARY
================================================================================

Renderflow is a spec-driven document rendering engine built in Rust. It
transforms Markdown source files into PDF and HTML outputs using Pandoc and
Tectonic, driven by a YAML configuration file. The codebase is clean,
modular, and well-tested with a clear separation of concerns.

The core pipeline is functional and ready for use. The primary areas of
concern are the incomplete template rendering system and the absence of
Cargo.lock from version control — an issue that affects reproducibility for
a binary application.

High-Level Readiness:
  - Core build pipeline (Markdown → HTML/PDF): READY
  - Template rendering (Tera integration):     INCOMPLETE
  - Audit / development workflow:              IN PROGRESS (this audit)
  - Plugin / transform extensibility:          PARTIAL (one transform only)

Major Risks:
  - Cargo.lock excluded from version control breaks reproducible builds
  - Template field declared but rendering logic not wired up

